pr-worktree-rm-merged-closed [--yes|-y] [--dry-run|-n]

Automatically delete every git worktree in the current repo that is safe
to discard without losing work. Two categories are removed:

  1. merged/closed PR — the branch has a GitHub PR in state `merged` or
     `closed`; leftover changes are treated as stale rebase/merge debris.
  2. no-pr + no-diff — the branch has no PR and no commits ahead of
     origin/main (git log --oneline origin/main..<branch> is empty); the
     worktree was created but never actually worked on.

Worktrees with an open PR, or with no PR but commits ahead of origin/main,
are LEFT ALONE. Use pr-worktree-rm for the interactive picker in those
cases.

Each worktree is removed with `git worktree remove`; on failure it retries
with `--force`. `git worktree prune` runs once at the end. The current
worktree and the main/primary worktree are always excluded.

Flags:
  --yes, -y       Skip the confirmation prompt (for cron / scripts).
  --dry-run, -n   List the worktrees that would be deleted and exit 0.

Requires: gh, git, jq.
